message.content:
1. There were two groups in the study.
2. The first group underwent SIRT.
3. The second group underwent TACE.
4. The SIRT group consisted of 8 males and 4 females.
5. The mean age of the SIRT group was 72 ± 7 years.
6. The TACE group consisted of 10 males and 2 females.
7. The mean age of the TACE group was 71 ± 9 years.
8. The demographics of both groups were comparable.
9. The initial tumor load was the same for both groups, with 1 patient having ≥25% in each group.
10. The BCLC stage for the SIRT group was 12×B.
11. The BCLC stage for the TACE group was 1×A, 11×B.
12. The BCLC stage was comparable for both groups.
13. BCLC stands for Barcelona Clinic Liver Cancer.

messages.content:
Statement: Both groups were comparable in demographics (SIRT: 8males/4females, mean age 72 ± 7 years; TACE: 10males/2females, mean age 71 ± 9 years), initial tumor load (1 patient ≥25 % in each group), and BCLC (Barcelona Clinic Liver Cancer) stage (SIRT: 12×B; TACE 1×A, 11×B).
